Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: It may be said that they are themselves possessed of sufficient funds for this purpose, in the tenth of land reserved for them; but it is worse than useless - it is cruel to talk of such a reserve, while at present much of it is not available, and very probably may not be so for a considerable time, in consequence of the difficult and therefore protracted nature of the surveys; and also from the absence of the Native Protector, as he is officially designated, who .. might by his presence here help to facilitate arrangements on behalf of the natives.
